Preconditions:
The input array `arr` must not be null.
The input array `arr` must contain at least 10 elements.

Postconditions:
The method should return a double value representing the mean of the remaining integers after removing the smallest 5% and the largest 5% of the elements.
The returned mean value should be rounded to two decimal places.
The original array `arr` should remain unchanged after the method is executed.